modules.description: Provides functions to format and manipulate text output, including padding, truncation, and alignment. Works with strings and formatted strings using a custom type for output specifications. Used to generate consistent log messages and user-facing output with precise control over width and alignment.

type t = { id: int; name: string; timestamp: float } Provides functions to create, update, and retrieve context metadata, including timestamp manipulation and identifier validation. Operates on structured records containing unique identifiers, string labels, and numeric time values. Used to manage session states in real-time applications and track event origins in distributed systems.

Encapsulates text formatting and context management capabilities, combining string manipulation with structured metadata handling. Supports operations like padding, truncation, and alignment on strings, and provides methods to construct, modify, and query records containing identifiers, names, and timestamps. Can generate aligned log entries and track session states with precise time and identity information. Examples include formatting user messages with fixed widths and annotating events with unique session IDs and timestamps.

Provides pattern matching and transformation operations for source code, supporting structured rewriting of syntax trees. Works with abstract syntax trees and textual representations of code. Enables precise refactoring of function calls and variable substitutions in codebases.

Manages text formatting and structured metadata, offering string alignment, padding, and truncation alongside record manipulation for identifiers, names, and timestamps. Enables creation of aligned log entries and session tracking with time and identity data. Formats user messages to fixed widths and annotates events with session IDs and timestamps. Supports precise control over text presentation and metadata enrichment.
